<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="265" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[811,1456,1268,1517]" box="[813,903,1268,1294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[811,1456,1268,1517]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
The Paris specimens identified 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Troschel" authorityYear="1842" box="[1138,1267,1299,1326]" class="Asteroidea" family="Archasteridae" genus="Archaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis box="[1138,1267,1299,1326]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">A. angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Muller &amp; Troschel" firstAuthor="Muller" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" refId="ref45916" refString="MULLER J. &amp; TROSCHEL H. 1842. - System der Asteriden. Braunschweig, 134 p." type="book" year="1842">Müller &amp; Troschel (1842)</bibRefCitation>
was collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[1147,1256,1331,1357]" name="Mauritius" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dujardin &amp; Hupe" firstAuthor="Dujardin" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" refId="ref43636" refString="DUJARDIN F. &amp; HUPE H. 1862. - Histoire naturelle des zoophytes echinodermes. Librairie encyclopedique De Roret, Paris, 625 p. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10122" type="book" year="1862">Dujardin &amp; Hupé (1862)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that individuals of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Troschel" authorityYear="1842" box="[1210,1338,1363,1390]" class="Asteroidea" family="Archasteridae" genus="Archaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis box="[1210,1338,1363,1390]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">A. angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
originated from either Java, 
<collectingCountry box="[1000,1107,1395,1421]" name="Mauritius" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
or 
<collectingCountry box="[1145,1294,1395,1422]" name="Australia" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">New Holland</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1309,1411,1395,1422]" name="Australia" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Australia</collectingCountry>
). In fact, three different 
<taxonomicName box="[1023,1197,1427,1453]" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis box="[1023,1118,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Archaster</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
inhabit these areas: Java (
<taxonomicName authority="Muller &amp; Troschel, 1840" authorityName="Muller &amp; Troschel" authorityYear="1840" box="[822,1203,1459,1485]" class="Asteroidea" family="Archasteridae" genus="Archaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="typicus">
<emphasis box="[822,922,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">A. typicus</emphasis>
Müller &amp; Troschel, 1840
</taxonomicName>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1223,1330,1459,1485]" name="Mauritius" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sukarno &amp; Jangoux" authorityYear="1977" box="[1346,1440,1459,1485]" class="Asteroidea" family="Archasteridae" genus="Archaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="lorioli">
<emphasis box="[1346,1440,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">A. lorioli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), west 
<collectingCountry box="[867,962,1491,1517]" name="Australia" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Troschel" authorityYear="1842" box="[978,1108,1491,1517]" class="Asteroidea" family="Archasteridae" genus="Archaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis box="[978,1108,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="265">A. angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Sukarno &amp; Jangoux" box="[1133,1410,1491,1517]" firstAuthor="Sukarno" pageId="8" pageNumber="265" pagination="817 - 844" refId="ref47081" refString="SUKARNO R. &amp; JANGOUX M. 1977. - Revision du genre Archaster Muller &amp; Troschel (Echinodermata: Asteroidea: Archasteridae). Revue de Zoologie africaine 91 (4): 817 - 844." type="journal article" year="1977">Sukarno &amp; Jangoux 1977</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
